description:
&lt;p&gt;The Main Theatres Department at Basildon Hospital is looking to appoint a Band 7 Clinical and Education Practice Facilitator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicant must be NMC or HCPC registered with a minimum of 5 years current clinical experience within an operating room setting. Experience in anaesthetics desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Clinical Practice Facilitator for Clinical Professional Development, you will enhance the quality of the practice learning experience within our Theatre Department and Day stay ward and positively contribute to the future nursing and Allied Health care professional workforce.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a proactive and knowledgeable leader in the field of education. An individual who is passionate about delivering high quality professional development for both pre and post registration learners. The post holder will have excellent communication and organisational skills and work collaboratively with all levels of staff in the theatre department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDenise ArcherJob titleLeadPractice and Education facilitatorEmail addressdenise.archer@btuh.nhs.ukTelephone number4937Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For an informal visit of further information please contact the Theatre Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Denise Archer – denise.archer@btuh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Extension 4937&lt;/p&gt;
